Class ToMap<K,V,M extends Map<K,V>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functions.builtin.fn2.ToMap<K,V,M>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key element type
    V - the value element type
    M - the resulting map type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Fn1<Supplier<M>,Fn1<Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>,M>>, Fn2<Supplier<M>,Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>,M>, Applicative<Fn1<Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>,M>,Fn1<Supplier<M>,?>>, Functor<Fn1<Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>,M>,Fn1<Supplier<M>,?>>, Profunctor<Supplier<M>,Fn1<Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>,M>,Fn1>, Function<Supplier<M>,Fn1<Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>,M>>

    public final class ToMap<K,V,M extends Map<K,V>>
extends Object
implements Fn2<Supplier<M>,Iterable<Map.Entry<K,V>>,M>
    Given a Supplier of some Map M, create an instance of M and put all of the entries in the provided Iterable into the instance. Note that instances of M must support Map.put(K, V) (which is to say, must not throw on invocation).
